# Hub Data Conventions

## Agent avatars: always the directory `icon_photo_url`

Every hub (Admin, Agent, Client, personal hubs, TV dashboards) renders agent
profile icons from the team directory's `agents.icon_photo_url` — never from
hardcoded CDN URLs, FUB, or Google auth photos.

- The photos are mirrored into Supabase Storage (`headshots/agents/{slug}-icon.*`)
  by `npm run photos:mirror-agents`; `agents.icon_photo_source` remembers the
  external URL each mirror came from so the directory sheet sync only replaces
  a photo when the sheet provides a genuinely new one.
- Frontends fetch `/api/directory` (or `/api/hub-data?view=directory`) and read
  `iconPhotoUrl` first, then `headshot`/`photo` as fallback. Hardcoded `TEAM`
  arrays in components must be overridden with directory photos at load
  (see `applyIconPhotoOverridesFromDirectory` in `admin-dashboard.html`).
- New surfaces showing an agent's face must follow the same cascade:
  `iconPhotoUrl → headshot → initials`.

## Deal/volume stats: always the "ASG Deals 2026" sheet, never FUB

Per-agent and team volume/deal counts shown on hub Overviews come from the
ASG Deals 2026 workbook maintained by transaction coordinators — FUB is not
the source of truth for production numbers.

- `refreshAgentStats()` (`apps/backend/src/sync/pipeline.ts`) imports the
  sheet's Apps Script stats endpoint (`env.DEALS_STATS_API`) into `agent_stats`
  on the pipeline cron; `/api/pipeline-stats` serves it to the hubs.
- Do not rewire `agent_stats`, `/api/pipeline-stats`, or Overview KPIs to
  FUB-derived tables (`deals`, `agent_volume`). FUB powers deal *workflow*
  surfaces (deal tracker checklists), not volume stats.
